---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Examples">
  <h1>Examples</h1>
  <p class="docs-subtitle">
    Two built-in packs to learn from — loadable via the studio's pack switcher.
  </p>

  <h2>Minimal Pack</h2>
  <p>
    The smallest valid soundtrack pack. One asset, one stem, one scene, one
    binding, zero transitions. Use it to understand the bare minimum data shape
    that passes validation and produces a working runtime export.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Entity</th><th>Count</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Assets</td><td>1</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Stems</td><td>1</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Scenes</td><td>1</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bindings</td><td>1</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Transitions</td><td>0</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    <strong>Key lesson:</strong> You don't need transitions to have a valid pack.
    Without transition rules, scene switches use an immediate hard cut by default.
  </p>

  <h2>Starter Adventure Pack</h2>
  <p>
    A mid-complexity pack with exploration, tension, combat, victory, and safe
    zone scenes. Demonstrates:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Optional layers with <code>mutedByDefault</code> and <code>gainDb</code> offsets</li>
    <li>Fallback scene chains (Victory → Exploration, Tension → Exploration)</li>
    <li>Four transition modes: crossfade, stinger-then-switch, immediate, cooldown-fade</li>
    <li>Priority-based binding resolution with <code>stopProcessing</code></li>
  </ul>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Entity</th><th>Count</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Assets</td><td>8</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Stems</td><td>7</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Scenes</td><td>5</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bindings</td><td>5</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Transitions</td><td>4</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    <strong>Key lesson:</strong> Multiple conditions per binding, fallback chains,
    and transition variety create a rich, believable adaptive soundtrack.
  </p>

  <h2>Loading examples in the studio</h2>
  <p>
    Use the <strong>Example Pack</strong> dropdown at the bottom of the sidebar
    to switch between packs. Switching reloads the entire pack — any unsaved
    edits to the current pack are lost.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
